{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    inner_grid = find_six_by_six_grid(input_grid)\n    output = cut_top_left_3x3(inner_grid)\n    return output\ndef find_six_by_six_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, this function returns a 6x6 grid containing all non-black points from the input grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the 6x6 grid containing all non-black points from the input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_black_points = input_grid[input_grid != black]\n    non_black_points = np.unique(non_black_points)\n    non_black_points = non_black_points[non_black_points != 0]\n    if len(non_black_points) > 36:\n        non_black_points = non_black_points[:36]\n    six_by_six_grid = np.zeros((6, 6))\n    for i, point in enumerate(non_black_points):\n        row = i // 6\n        col = i % 6\n        six_by_six_grid[row][col] = point\n    return six_by_six_grid\ndef cut_top_left_3x3(inner_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an inner grid, this function returns a 3x3 grid containing the top-left 3x3 points from the input grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    inner_grid: A numpy array representing the inner grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the 3x3 grid containing the top-left 3x3 points from the input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    return inner_grid[:3, :3]", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n\tinner_grid = `find a 6*6 grid which contain all not-black point in input_grid`(input_grid)\n\toutput = `cut a 3*3 grid from top-left in inner_grid`(inner_grid)\n\treturn output\n\t\n\t", "gpt_code": "def find_six_by_six_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, this function returns a 6x6 grid containing all non-black points from the input grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the inp